Shadow Double	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.ShadowAdeptClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Once per day, a shadow adept can use a standard action to create a double of himself woven from shadowstuff. The double has the ability scores, base AC, hit points, saves and attack bonuses as its creator, but not equipment (Any apparent clothing or equipment is nonfunctional). The double can attack the creator's enemies if given a weapon or items (since it can use anything its creator can or function as the target of a project image spell), duplicating the creator's actions and acting as the origin of the creator's spells when it is within direct line of sight. Mentally commanding the double is a free action. Using it as the originator of a spell counts as an action for the creator and the double. Causing the creator or the double to leave the plane they share dismisses the double. The double lasts 1 round per caster level. The death of the double does not affect the shadow adept or vice versa. The double still lasts to the end of its duration if its creator dies.	KEY:Shadow Adept ~ Shadow Double																										SORTKEY:Class_Shadow_Adept	SOURCEPAGE:FRCS30		
